article.headline: Hofstra 82, William & Mary 57
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Loren Stokes scored 19 points and Antoine Agudio added 16 as Hofstra beat William & Mary 82-57 on Monday night. Aurimas Kieza and Adrian Uter added 14 for the Pride (20-5, 12-4 Colonial Athletic Association). Kieza scored 10 straight during a 12-2 run that put Hofstra ahead 66-43 with 10:17 remaining. Hofstra led by as many as 28 the rest of the way. Hofstra jumped out to a 12-2 lead, but William & Mary (8-17, 3-13) cut that to 17-15 off a 13-5 run capped by back-to-back layups by Peter Stein. Hofstra again stretched its lead to 10 and led 33-42 at halftime. Hofstra shot 73.9 percent in the first half and 56.1 percent for the game, compared to 37.5 percent shooting for the Tribe. Calvin Baker was the only William & Mary player to score in double figures with 14 points. The Tribe were outrebounded 37-24. Uter set a school record for consecutive field goals made. He made 6 of 6, all in the first half, after hitting his final 12 shots in Saturday's win over Siena. The 18 straight baskets also is seven shy of the NCAA record, which has stood since 1978.
